snippet.title: 'Objectify a Male Tech Writer Day' gets canned
snippet.description: Unmark your calendar for February 1. Objectify a Male Tech Writer day has been canceled due to potential misunderstandings and misuse.

snippet.title: Get ready for 'Objectify a Male Tech Writer Day'
snippet.description: February 1 has been deemed a day for adding comments about the appearance of male tech writers when sharing their articles. The aim? Opening a discussion on how women tech writers are sometimes treated.

snippet.title: Facebook under fire (again) for all-male board
snippet.description: The fact that the social-networking site doesn't have any women on its board "is nothing short of shameful," says the newest advocacy group to join the FACE IT campaign.

snippet.title: Silicon Power Armor A80 review: Double A(lpha) male
snippet.description: CNET editor Dong Ngo finds a portable hard drive that impresses even him, though the Silicon Power Armor A80 has one quirk.

snippet.title: Ohio male may be linked to LulzSec attacks
snippet.description: A male from Saint Clair Township in Ohio is under investigation for possible involvement in recent hacking attacks launched against governments Web sites in the U.S. and U.K., say Ohio news sources.

snippet.title: Survey: Android adoption skews heavily male
snippet.description: A recent study conducted in the United Kingdom reveals that very few women know about Android or how it can help them.

snippet.title: A troubling slur on male nerd sexuality
snippet.description: Researchers at the University of Sydney have declared that male science students are the least likely to have sex. But a very small proportion of the respondents were actually male.

snippet.title: Soon, billboards that know male from female
snippet.description: Technology out of Singapore is focused on advertising, so future digital billboards can detect the gender of the person looking at it and display the appropriate ad. Next up: age recognition.

snippet.title: Sony Alpha A900: Full-frame Alpha male
snippet.description: The Sony Alpha A900, the first full-frame model from Sony, has finally been made official. It packs a whopping 24.6-megapixel resolution on that giant sensor

snippet.title: Shock! Scientists say video games feed male need to dominate
snippet.description: Stanford researchers declare that video game playing stimulates parts of the male brain that delight in stomping on others.
